{{Orphan|date=February 2015}}
{{Infobox company | name = grouptime GmbH | logo = | type = [[Privately held company|Private]] | industry = [[Information Technology]] | location_city = [[Munich]] | location_country = Germany | foundation = 2010 | key_people = [[Tobias Stepan]] | products = Teamwire | homepage = [http://www.teamwire.eu/ teamwire.eu] }}
'''Grouptime''' is a technology start-up based in Munich, Germany, and focused on mobile messaging apps. The core product is Teamwire, an encrypted [[instant messaging]] app for enterprises and the public sector. In addition to text messaging, users can send photos, videos, locations, voice messages and files with Teamwire.
== History ==
The company was founded in August 2010 in Munich (Germany) by Tobias Stepan. In September 2011 the grouptime app was officially launched for devices with Apple`s iOS.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appleview.de/grouptime-neue-kostenlose-messenger-app-fuer-iphone-und-ipod/|title=Grouptime: Neue kostenlose Messenger App für iPhone und iPod (German Article)|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2011/9/prweb8787493.htm|title=Grouptime iPhone App Offers Instant Group Messaging, Sharing and Status Updates|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> In 2012 several updates of the app were released to improve group messaging and sharing of digital content.
In March 2014 grouptime launched a secure enterprise messaging app called [http://www.teamwire.eu/ Teamwire] to simplify and improve the internal communication.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressebox.de/pressemitteilung/mobileiron/MobileIron-AppConnect-Partner-Teamwire-Sicheres-Messaging-fuer-Unternehmen-nach-deutschen-Datenschutzanforderungen/boxid/662967.htm|title=Secure Enterprise Messaging with German Data Protection (German article)|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> The idea was to provide a messenger for businesses, to replace the email as the dominant channel for team communication. By mid of 2014 grouptime abandoned its consumer product and completely focussed on the enterprise messaging market. In January 2015 in addition to the German cloud Teamwire became also available as an on-premise and private cloud deployment in order to fulfill the strong data protection requirements of enterprises, large corporations and the public sector.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teamwire.eu/on-premise-deployment-of-teamwire/|title=Teamwire offers on-premises solution for enterprise messaging|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> In March 2016 Teamwire became a cross-platform enterprise messaging app with the release of apps for desktop devices like Windows, Mac and Linux in addition to the existing iOS and Android apps.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2016/03/prweb13250528.htm|title=Teamwire Releases Secure Enterprise Messaging App for Desktop Devices|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>
In January 2017 the largest German financial services group deployed Teamwire as a secure messenger for the bank.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.f-i.de/content/download/18469/233338/file/itm_0117_gesamt.pdf|title=My Mobile Office of the Sparkassen Financial Services Group (German Article)|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref> In May 2017 it became public that the police in the state of Bavaria in Germany uses Teamwire as a secure alternative to [[WhatsApp]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.heise.de/newsticker/meldung/Bayern-Neuer-Polizei-Messenger-fuer-Streifenbeamte-3725791.html|title=New Messenger for the Police (German Article)|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.welt.de/regionales/bayern/article167101993/Die-bayerische-Polizei-wird-aufgeruestet-mit-iPhones.html|title=Bavarian Police Is Equipped with Own Messenger (German Article)|postscript=<!--None-->}}</ref>
