{{other uses}} {{Use mdy dates|date=July 2015}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Mr. Robot | image = MrRobot intertitle.png | genre = {{Plainlist| * [[Drama]] * [[Techno thriller]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcumv.com/programming/usa-network/mr-robot/about?network=33145 |title=About |publisher=NBCUniversal Media Village |accessdate=August 20, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://nerdist.com/christian-slater-on-the-programming-of-mr-robot/ |title=Christian Slater on the Programming of MR. ROBOT |publisher=Nerdist |first=Joseph |last=McCabe |date=July 5, 2015 |accessdate=August 20, 2015}}</ref> * {{nowrap|[[Psychological thriller]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-ca-st-tvpreview-robot-20150531-story.html |title=Wealth disparity, hackers and cyber threats in 'Mr. Robot' |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |first=Alan |last=Eyerly |date=May 29, 2015 |accessdate=July 3, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/06/18/mr-robot-ew-review |title=''Mr. Robot'': EW review |work=Entertainment Weekly |first=Jeff |last=Jensen |date=June 18, 2015 |accessdate=July 3, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.usanetwork.com/node/56611 |title=Mr. Robot |publisher=USA Network |accessdate=August 21, 2015}}</ref>}}}} | creator = [[Sam Esmail]] | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Rami Malek]] * [[Carly Chaikin]] * [[Portia Doubleday]] * [[Martin Wallström]] * [[Christian Slater]] * [[Michael Cristofer]] * [[Stephanie Corneliussen]] * [[Grace Gummer]] * [[BD Wong]] * [[Bobby Cannavale]] }} | composer = Mac Quayle<ref>{{cite web |last=Horner |first=Al |url=http://www.factmag.com/2016/06/07/how-to-soundtrack-a-cyber-terrorist-revolution-mr-robot/ |title=How to soundtrack a cyber-anarchic revolution, by ''Mr Robot'' composer Mac Quayle |work=FACT |date=June 7, 2016 |accessdate=June 9, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fuse.tv/2017/05/mac-quayle-interview-composer-american-horror-story-mr-robot-feud |title=Composer Mac Quayle Talks 'American Horror Story,' 'Mr. Robot' & Going From Dance to Darkness |work=Fuse |first=Bianca |last=Gracie |date=May 25, 2017 |accessdate=June 10, 2017}}</ref> | country = United States | language = English | num_seasons = 3<!--Update this only when seasons premiere.--> | num_episodes = 32<!--Update this only when episodes air.--> | list_episodes = List of Mr. Robot episodes | executive_producer = {{Plainlist| * Sam Esmail * [[Steve Golin]] * Chad Hamilton * Joseph E. Iberti <small>(season 3)</small> * Kyle Bradstreet <small>(season 3)</small> }} | producer = {{Plainlist| * Igor Srubshchik * Christian Slater * Rami Malek <small>(season 3)</small> }} | location = [[New York City]] | cinematography = {{Plainlist| * Tim Ives {{small|(pilot)}} * Tod Campbell }} | camera = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]] | runtime = 41–65 minutes | company = {{Plainlist| * [[Universal Cable Productions]] * [[Anonymous Content]] * Esmail Corp {{small|(season 2–present)}} }} | distributor = [[NBCUniversal Television Distribution]] | picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[16:9]] [[High-definition television|HDTV]]) | first_aired = {{start date|2015|6|24}} | last_aired = {{end date|present}} | website = http://www.usanetwork.com/mrrobot | website_title = Official website | channel = [[USA Network]] }}
'''''Mr. Robot''''' is an American [[thriller (genre)|drama thriller]] television series created by [[Sam Esmail]]. It stars [[Rami Malek]] as Elliot Alderson, a [[computer security|cybersecurity]] engineer and [[Security hacker|hacker]] who has [[social anxiety disorder]] and [[clinical depression]]. Elliot is recruited by an [[insurrectionary anarchism|insurrectionary anarchist]] known as "Mr. Robot", played by [[Christian Slater]], to join a group of [[hacktivism|hacktivists]] called "fsociety".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/la-en-st-mr-robot-20170525-story.html|title='Mr. Robot' hews close to current events, sometimes so close it's 'an out-of-body experience'|date=May 25, 2017|work=Los Angeles Times|first=Steve|last=Dollar|access-date=June 10, 2017|issn=0458-3035}}</ref> The group aims to destroy all debt records by [[Encryption|encrypting]] the financial data of the largest [[Conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]] in the world, E&nbsp;Corp.
The pilot premiered on multiple online and [[video on demand]] services on May 27, 2015. The first season premiered on [[USA Network]] on June 24, 2015, and the second on July 13, 2016. The 10-episode third season premiered on October 11, 2017. In December 2017, ''Mr. Robot'' was renewed for a fourth season.<!--Per WP:CITELEAD, references are not needed in the lead if it is sourced in the body of the article!--> In August 2018, it was confirmed that the fourth season, to air in 2019 and consisting of 12 episodes, will be the final season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/mr-robot-end-season-4-usa-network-1137204 |title='Mr. Robot' to End With Season 4 on USA Network (Exclusive) |work=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |date=August 29, 2018 |accessdate=August 29, 2018}}</ref>
''Mr. Robot'' has received critical acclaim and has been nominated for and won multiple awards, including the [[Golden Globe Award for Best Television Series&nbsp;– Drama|Golden Globe for Best Television Drama Series]] and was recognized with a [[Peabody Award]]. In 2016, the series received six [[Primetime Emmy Awards|Emmy]] nominations, including Outstanding Drama Series with Malek winning for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/artisans/production/mr-robot-editing-1202449276/|title=‘Mr. Robot’ Editing Style Reflects Chaotic View of Main Character|last=Galas|first=Marj|date=June 2, 2017|work=Variety|access-date=June 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goldderby.com/article/2017/rami-malek-mr-robot-best-drama-actor-2017-emmys-entertainment-news/|title=Rami Malek (‘Mr. Robot’) could become 9th Best Drama Actor to win consecutive Emmy Awards|last=Buchanan|first=David|date=May 18, 2017|work=Goldderby|access-date=June 10, 2017}}</ref> {{TOC limit|3}}
==Premise== {{further|List of Mr. Robot episodes}} The series follows Elliot Alderson, a young man living in [[New York City]], who works at the cyber security company Allsafe as a [[Security engineering|security engineer]]. Constantly struggling with [[social anxiety disorder]], [[dissociative identity disorder]] and [[clinical depression]], Elliot's thought process seems heavily influenced by [[paranoia]] and [[delusion]].<ref name="wsj">{{cite web |url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2015/07/15/mr-robot-star-rami-malek-dives-into-a-world-of-paranoia-addiction-and-illusion/ |title=‘Mr. Robot’ Star Rami Malek Dives Into a World of Paranoia, Addiction and Illusion |work=The Wall Street Journal |first=John |last=Jurgensen |date=July 15, 2015 |accessdate=August 20, 2015}}</ref> He connects to people by [[Security hacker|hacking]] them, which often leads him to act as a cyber-[[vigilante]]. He is recruited by a mysterious [[Insurrectionary anarchism|insurrectionary anarchist]] known as Mr. Robot and joins his team of [[hacktivists]] known as ''fsociety''. One of their missions is to cancel all [[consumer debt]] by destroying the data of one of the largest corporations in the world, E Corp (which Elliot perceives as Evil Corp), which also happens to be Allsafe's biggest client.<ref name=Deadline-MrRobotS2-Renewal-2015>{{cite news|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=‘Mr. Robot’ Gets Second-Season Pickup By USA Ahead Of Series Premiere|url=https://deadline.com/2015/06/mr-robot-renewed-season-2-usa-1201453623/|accessdate=July 4, 2015|publisher=Deadline.com|date=June 24, 2015}}</ref> {{:List of Mr. Robot episodes}}
