The '''Sri Lanka Sustainable Energy Authority''' (or '''SLSEA''') is the primary body responsible for the issuance of licenses for [[sustainable energy]] developments in [[Sri Lanka]]. In addition to being the key licence provider, it is also the organization responsible for promoting [[renewable energy]] and sustainable developments in the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=About SLSEA|url=http://www.energy.gov.lk/sub_pgs/aboutus_who.html|publisher=Sri Lanka Sustainable Energy Authority|accessdate=16 January 2014}}</ref>
